Two aspects of brain structure make it difficult to pass on our subjective experience to that of animals.
First, they almost always include the circuits associated with human consciousness of the lateral prefrontal lobe of the cerebral cortex (because of their involvement in short memory and executive functions that direct behavior).
This large part is much more developed in the case of people than that of the other primates and seems to be absolutely lacking in other creatures.
