The German Gónther Bauer alternates in "Flamenco-people" the theatricality of some stagings with singers, dancers and guitarists with that lesser known side of these masters.
With this proposal, the photographer collects the particular iconography of flamenco from different areas.
Included in the program of Flemish Photography Month, the exhibition "reflects the international importance of flamenco, increasing every day", explains the creator, who clarifies that "Flamenco-people" can be anyone but, when viewing the photos, the observer realizes that they are not the typical images of artists on stage.
